	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Coating_layer  
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Coating_layer"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Coating_layer">
A <b>Coating_layer</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Shape_property_assignment:arm:Shape_property_assignment_arm.Shape_element"/> that identifies a layer of covering applied to a surface.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Coating_layer  Attribute: thickness
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Coating_layer.thickness"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Coating_layer.thickness">
the <express_ref linkend="Dimension_tolerance:arm:Dimension_tolerance_arm.Thickness_size"/> that refers to the <b>Coating_layer</b> and specifies its <b>thickness</b>. There may not be any <b>thickness</b> specified.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Coating_layer  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Coating_layer.wr:WR1"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Coating_layer.wr:WR1">
A <b>Coating_layer</b> shall be referred to by exactly one <express_ref linkend="Generic_material_aspects:arm:Generic_material_aspects_arm.Material_identification"/> that identifies the coating material.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Contact_ratio  
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Contact_ratio"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Contact_ratio">
A <b>Contact_ratio</b> is a type of  <express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition"/> that specifies the measure of the quality of contact of a shape on a reference surface. It is expressed as the ratio between the measure of the area of contact and the measure of the area of the reference surface.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Contact_ratio  Attribute: ratio_value 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Contact_ratio.ratio_value"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Contact_ratio.ratio_value">
a value between 0.0 and 1.0 that is the ratio between the measure of the area of contact and the measure of the area of the reference surface.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Contact_ratio  Attribute: measuring_gauge 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Contact_ratio.measuring_gauge"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Contact_ratio.measuring_gauge">
	a  
	<express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.measuring_gauge_select"/> 
	that serves as the reference for the determination of a <b>Contact_ratio</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- name -->
<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Contact_ratio.name">
	an inherited attribute shall be the
	string with value 'contact ratio'
	for the <b>Contact_ratio</b>.
</ext_description>

	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Hardness  
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Hardness"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Hardness">
A <b>Hardness</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition"/> that defines the hardness of a material on its surface. The <b>Hardness</b> represents the resistance of a surface to deformation by external forces.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Hardness  Attribute: measuring_method 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Hardness.measuring_method"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Hardness.measuring_method">
		<p>the method for measuring <b>Hardness</b> values. 

Where applicable the following values shall be used: </p>
		<ul>
			<li>'brinell': The <b>Hardness</b> is measured according to the Brinell method;</li>
			<li>'rockwell': The <b>Hardness</b> is measured according to the Rockwell method;</li>
			<li>'vickers': The <b>Hardness</b> is measured according to the Vickers method.</li>
		</ul>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Hardness  Attribute: environment_condition 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Hardness.environment_condition"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Hardness.environment_condition">
the conditions under that the specified <b>hardness_value</b> is valid.
</ext_description>
	
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Hardness  Attribute: measuring_position 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Hardness.measuring_position"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Hardness.measuring_position">
		<p>the position where the <b>Hardness</b> is measured with respect to the part of interest.</p>
		<example number="1">
			'core' or 'surface' are examples for <b>measuring_position</b> where 'core' is inside the hardened part, i.e., it is measured before a 
			quenching process, and 'surface' is on the surface of a hardened part, i.e., it is measured after a quenching process.
		</example>
		<p>The value of this attribute need not be specified.</p>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Hardness  Attribute: hardness_value 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Hardness.hardness_value"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Hardness.hardness_value">
the value of the <b>Hardness</b>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Hardness  Attribute: depth 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Hardness.depth"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Hardness.depth">
		<p>the layer measured from the surface into the material where the specified <b>Hardness</b> applies. </p>
		<example number="2">The layer of the hardened material after a high-frequency quenching process is an example for <b>depth</b>.</example>
		<p>The value of this attribute need not be specified.</p>
	</ext_description>
	
	<!-- name -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Hardness.name">
		an inherited attribute shall be the 
		string with value 'hardness'
		for the <b>Hardness</b>.
	</ext_description>
	
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Surface_condition  
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition">
	A <b>Surface_condition</b> is a type of
	<express_ref linkend="Shape_property_assignment:arm:Shape_property_assignment_arm.Assigned_shape_property"/>.
	A <b>Surface_condition</b> is a definition of a characteristic or property of a surface of an item.
	<note>
		A <b>Surface_condition</b> may be specified during the design phase of a product as an expected characteristic of the parts resulting from 
		the manufacturing process, but it may also be documented as measured on a prototype.
	</note>
	Each <b>Surface_condition</b> is either a
	<express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Contact_ratio"/>,
	a
	<express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Hardness"/>,
	a
	<express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture"/>,
	a
	<express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Tactile_appearance"/>,
	a
	<express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Treatment_result"/>,
	or a
	<express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Visual_appearance"/>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Surface_condition  Attribute: value_determination 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition.value_determination"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition.value_determination">
	<p>
		classification information on how the <b>Surface_condition</b> shall be interpreted without giving details.
		Where applicable the following values shall be used:		
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>'calculated': The value has been calculated from a digital representation;</li>
		<li>'designed': The value represents a value intended by the design;</li>
		<li>'estimated': The value has been estimated;</li>
		<li>'measured': The value has been measured on a manufactured part;</li>
		<li>'required': The value represents a requirement.</li>
	</ul>
		<p>The value of this attribute need not be specified.</p>
	</ext_description>
	
	<!-- described_element -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition.described_element">
		specifies the object that is characterized by the <b>Surface_condition</b>.
	</ext_description>
	
	<!-- generic_representation -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition.generic_representation">
		 specifies an inverse relationship that specifies that the existence of the <b>Surface_condition</b> is dependent on the existence of the 
		 <express_ref linkend="Property_assignment:arm:Property_assignment_arm.Property_definition_representation"/> 
		 that specifies the <b>Surface_condition</b> as its 
		 <express_ref linkend="Property_assignment:arm:Property_assignment_arm.Property_definition_representation.definition"/>.
		 There should be no
		 <express_ref linkend="Property_assignment:arm:Property_assignment_arm.Property_definition_representation">Property_definition_representations</express_ref> 
		 for this <b>Surface_condition</b>.
	</ext_description>
	
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Surface_condition_association  
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition_association"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition_association">
A <b>Surface_condition_association</b> is a mechanism to associate a <express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition"/> with an instance.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Surface_condition_association  Attribute: describing_surface_condition 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition_association.describing_surface_condition"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition_association.describing_surface_condition">
the condition of a surface that is being assigned to an instance.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Surface_condition_association  Attribute: described_element 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition_association.described_element"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition_association.described_element">
the instance that is characterized by the <express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition"/>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Surface_texture  
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture">
A <b>Surface_texture</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition"/> that characterizes of irregularities of the surface of a shape or of a portion of a shape. Such an irregularity has a negligible impact on its dimensions but may impact some of its mechanical or functional characteristics.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Surface_texture  Attribute: measuring_method 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture.measuring_method"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture.measuring_method">
		<p>the method or standard that describes the method used to characterize the <b>Surface_texture</b>. 

Where applicable the following values shall be used: </p>
		<ul>
			<li>'ISO 4287': The used surface texture parameters are defined in ISO 4287; </li>
			<li>'ISO 12085': The used surface texture parameters are defined in ISO 12085; </li>
			<li>'ISO 13565': The used surface texture parameters are defined in ISO 13565. </li>
		</ul>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Surface_texture  Attribute: measuring_direction 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture.measuring_direction"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture.measuring_direction">
	the 
	<express_ref linkend="Dimension_tolerance:arm:Dimension_tolerance_arm.Measurement_path"/> 
	in which the <b>Surface_texture</b> is measured on actual parts.
	The value of this attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>

<!-- parameters -->
<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture.parameters">
	specifies the set of
	<express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture_parameter"/> 
	for the  <b>Surface_texture</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- name -->
<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture.name">
	an inherited attribute shall be the
	string with value 'surface texture'
	for the <b>Surface_texture</b>.
</ext_description>

	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Surface_texture_parameter  
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture_parameter"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture_parameter">
A <b>Surface_texture_parameter</b> is a combination of a parameter name and possibly parameter values describing one particular parameter of a <express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture"/> such as roughness or waviness.
The meaning of the <b>Surface_texture_parameter</b> is defined by the measuring method.

<example number="1">A typical <b>Surface_texture_parameter</b> according to ISO 4287 is Ra; in this case, the parameter name is 'R' and the parameter value is 'a'.</example>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Surface_texture_parameter  Attribute: parameter_value 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture_parameter.parameter_value"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture_parameter.parameter_value">
the value of the <b>Surface_texture_parameter</b>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Surface_texture_parameter  Attribute: parameter_name 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture_parameter.parameter_name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture_parameter.parameter_name">
		<p>the word or group of words by which the <b>Surface_texture_parameter</b> is referred.</p>
		<example number="2">
			<p>Parameter names defined in ISO 4287 are sampling or evaluation length 'l', primary profile parameter 'P', roughness profile parameter 'R', and waviness profile parameter 'W'. </p>
			<p>Parameter values defined in ISO 4287 are maximum peak height 'p', maximum valley depth 'v', maximum height 'y', mean height 'c', total height 't', arithmetical mean deviation 'a', and root mean square deviation 'q'.</p>
		</example>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Surface_texture_parameter  Attribute: described_texture 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture_parameter.described_texture"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture_parameter.described_texture">
the <express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture"/> that is described by the <b>Surface_texture_parameter</b>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Surface_texture_parameter  Attribute: parameter_index 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture_parameter.parameter_index"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_texture_parameter.parameter_index">
an index that specifies the name of the <b>Surface_texture_parameter</b> further.
The <b>parameter_index</b> need not be specified for a particular <b>Surface_texture_parameter</b>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Tactile_appearance  
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Tactile_appearance"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Tactile_appearance">
A <b>Tactile_appearance</b>  is a type of 
<express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition"/> 
that specifies the appearance of a surface of a part regarding the sense of touch.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Tactile_appearance  Attribute: id 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Tactile_appearance.id"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Tactile_appearance.id">
	the identifier of the <b>Tactile_appearance</b>. 
	The value of this attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Tactile_appearance  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Tactile_appearance.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Tactile_appearance.name">
	an inherited attribute shall be the
	string with value 'tactile appearance'
	the <b>Tactile_appearance</b>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Tactile_appearance  Attribute: depth 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Tactile_appearance.depth"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Tactile_appearance.depth">
		<p>the extent of the <b>Tactile_appearance</b> in the normal direction of the surface. </p>
		<note>
			The interpretation of the depth depends on the definition of the <b>Tactile_appearance</b>, i.e., 
			on the contents of the attribute description.
		</note>
		<p>The value of this attribute need not be specified.</p>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Tactile_appearance  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Tactile_appearance.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Tactile_appearance.description">
	additional information about the <b>Tactile_appearance</b>. 
	The value of this attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Treatment_result  
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Treatment_result"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Treatment_result">
	A <b>Treatment_result</b> is a type of 
	<express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition"/> 
	that is a result of a certain treatment.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Treatment_result  Attribute: id 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Treatment_result.id"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Treatment_result.id">
	the identifier of the <b>Treatment_result</b>. 
	The value of this attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Treatment_result  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Treatment_result.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Treatment_result.name">
	an inherited attribute shall be the
	string with value 'treatment result'
	the <b>Treatment_result</b>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Treatment_result  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Treatment_result.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Treatment_result.description">
	additional information about the <b>Treatment_result</b>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Treatment_result  Attribute: purpose 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Treatment_result.purpose"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Treatment_result.purpose">
	the effects that are a consequence of the treatment. 
	The value of this attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Visual_appearance  
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Visual_appearance"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Visual_appearance">
	A <b>Visual_appearance</b> is a type of 
	<express_ref linkend="Surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Surface_condition"/> 
	that specifies the appearance of a surface of a part regarding the optical impression.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Visual_appearance  Attribute: colour_id 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Visual_appearance.colour_id"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Surface_conditions_arm.Visual_appearance.colour_id">
	<p>the identifier of the colour of the <b>Visual_appearance</b>. </p>
	<example number="1">A colour can be identified using a code such as 'C130202250'.</example>
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Surface_conditions_arm  Entity: Visual_appearance  Attribute: lustre 
   <express_ref linkend="surface_conditions:arm:Surface_conditions_arm.Visual_appearance.lustre"/>
